Slack <code>*.dmg</code> file for MacOS takes <strong>168 MiB</strong>.</p>
<h2 id="seriously">Seriously</h2>
<p>Weechat itself is just <strong>26 MiB</strong>. It also really is lightweight and
feels fast. The number of extension is just countless. Number of color themes and layouts is huge too.</p>
<p>The 219 MiB comes from dependencies and you can see there are few programming languages are going to be installed:</p>
<ul>
<li>perl</li>
<li>lua</li>
<li>ruby</li>
<li>tcl</li>
</ul>
<p>These are not direct dependencies of weechat. It&rsquo;s just weechat&rsquo;s extension system allows you to use many programming languages to write extensions.</p>